parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The flickering/pulsing of headlights when braking can cause confusion to other drivers, potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: Headlights flicker or pulse when braking
especially at night
making it difficult to see the road ahead.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inadequate alternator output can cause the headlights to dim or fail, leading to reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Headlights dim or flicker when braking
especially at night
and may eventually fail.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A dead battery can leave the driver stranded, and frequent battery drain can be a safety concern.
symptoms: Battery dies frequently
especially after replacing the battery
and may be related to the alternator output issue.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS module can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: ABS module failure
causing brake problems
and may not show any warning lights.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A failed horn can reduce the driver's ability to alert other drivers, pedestrians, or cyclists, potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: Horn failure
making it difficult to alert others.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The flickering or pulsing of headlights when braking can cause reduced visibility, distractions, and potentially lead to accidents, especially at night or in low-light conditions.
symptoms: Headlights flicker or pulse when applying the brakes
headlights dim and then brighten
headlights flash rapidly
and nearby cars may be distracted or think the vehicle is signaling them.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water ingress into the headlight assembly can cause the headlights to malfunction, leading to reduced visibility and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: Water accumulates in the headlight assembly
headlights short out or malfunction
and the light bulb may need to be replaced frequently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the TCM can cause the transmission to malfunction, leading to sudden loss of power, jerking, and clunking noises, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The AT light comes on
the transmission makes a jerking or clunking noise
the vehicle loses power
the transmission shifts erratically
the check engine light is illuminated
and the vehicle may stall or fail to shift gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission valve body can cause the transmission to malfunction, leading to sudden loss of power, jerking, and clunking noises, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission shifts erratically
the vehicle loses power
the transmission makes a jerking or clunking noise
the check engine light is illuminated
and the vehicle may stall or fail to shift gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch can cause the transmission to malfunction, leading to sudden loss of power, jerking, and clunking noises, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
and the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the transmission to malfunction, leading to sudden loss of power, jerking, and clunking noises, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The headlights flicker
the vehicle's lights flash
the instrument cluster lights flash
and the vehicle's electrical system malfunctions.
